    <text>
        <body>
            <div type="edition">
                <div type="textpart">
                    <ab>In nomine Domini. Anno ab incarnacione eius millesimo centesimo quadragesimo
                        octavo, die decima mensis augusti, indictione undecima, <placeName
                            ref="#places/4179">Pomposea</placeName>. Petisti a me in Dei nomine
                        domno <persName key="#Abbots" ref="#people/4310">Iohanne</persName>
                        venerabile <rs key="#Abbots">abbate</rs>
                        <rs key="#Monasteries">monasterii</rs>
                        <orgName key="#Libellus/precaria/emphyteusis #Houses #Rivers #Marshes/lagoons/tombolos #Fundi #Casalia #Landed_possessions #Forests #Fisheries #Production #Cereals #Maiores #Minores #Wine #Hay/fodder #Linen #Levies #Rights_of_use_on_woods/pastures/waters #Districtio #Monasteries" ref="#juridical_persons/1460">Sancte Marie que
                            vocatur a Pomposea</orgName>, cum consensu monachorum eiusdem
                        monasterii, uti tibi presenti in Christi nomine <persName><name
                                ref="Deusdedit">Deodatus</name></persName> petitore, pro te et
                        iugale tua et pro vestris liberis et heredibus, per <rs
                            key="#Libellus/precaria/emphyteusis">libellum</rs> concedo vobis totum
                        quod abetis et detinetis et vobis pertinet infra toto <rs key="#Fundi"
                            >fundo</rs> de <geogName
                            key="#Libellus/precaria/emphyteusis #Houses #Rivers #Marshes/lagoons/tombolos #Fundi #Casalia #Landed_possessions #Forests #Fisheries #Production #Cereals #Maiores #Minores #Wine #Hay/fodder #Linen #Levies #Rights_of_use_on_woods/pastures/waters #Districtio"
                            ref="#estates/3927">
                                <placeName key="#Libellus/precaria/emphyteusis #Houses #Rivers #Marshes/lagoons/tombolos #Fundi #Casalia #Landed_possessions #Forests #Fisheries #Production #Cereals #Maiores #Minores #Wine #Hay/fodder #Linen #Levies #Rights_of_use_on_woods/pastures/waters #Districtio" ref="#places/4685">Medio Gauro</placeName></geogName>, <rs
                            key="#Houses">casis</rs>, <rs key="#Casalia">casalibus</rs>, <rs
                            key="#Landed_possessions">terris</rs>, <rs key="#Production"
                        >campis</rs>, <rs key="#Hay/fodder">pascuis</rs>, <rs key="#Forests"
                            >silvis</rs>, <rs key="#Rivers">aquis</rs>, <rs
                            key="#Marshes/lagoons/tombolos">paludibus</rs>, <rs key="#Fisheries"
                            >piscacionibus</rs>, <rs key="#Rights_of_use_on_woods/pastures/waters"
                            >venacionibus</rs>, cum omnibus suis pertinenciis; abendum, tenendum,
                        supersedendum, per te vel per filium tuum cultandum, laborandum, piscandum,
                        venandum, augelandum et in omnibus meliorandum in annis advenientibus
                        viginti et novem ad renovandum. <rs key="#Levies">Terraticum</rs> nobis dare
                        debeatis, omni anni, in campo de <rs key="#Cereals #Maiores">grano</rs>
                        cappa quinta, <rs key="#Cereals #Maiores">sicale</rs> et <rs key="#Legumes"
                            >faba</rs> in campo cappa sexta, traenda ad area in garnato et <rs
                            key="#Cereals #Minores">trisico</rs> et <rs key="#Cereals #Minores"
                            >milio</rs> in area stario octavo, <rs key="#Linen">lino</rs> manna
                        octava, <rs key="#Wine">vino</rs> anfora quarta, arbore semel ponenda; si
                        vineam plantaveritis extra casale, fruere debeatis postquam in perticam
                        pervenerit annos tres et postea reddere debeatis anfora quarta; tritulatum
                        et pervectum omne restum per vos <rs key="#Fluvial_transport">usque ad ripam
                            Sancti Benedicti</rs>; non debeatis triturare neque vindemiare sine
                        iussione nostra, nos et nostrum missum cum onore et obediencia susipere
                        debeatis … dacionem et reddita nobis facere debeatis secundum usum ipsius
                        loci … de <rs key="#Forests">silva</rs> et de <rs
                            key="#Marshes/lagoons/tombolos">valle</rs>
                        <rs key="#Land_clearing">rescucieritis</rs> fruere debeatis annos tres
                        postea … ut alii redditus non licet vobis neque vestris filiis predictas res
                        nec … nec vendere, nec donare, nec ullo modo alienare nisi inter vestros
                        consortes, nec in guardia nec commendacione alicuius mittere nec <rs
                            key="#Districtio">ad ullum placitum ire nisi ad nostrum</rs>. Pro
                        calciario dedisti nobis exinde denariorum Lucensium solidos treginta et
                        unum. Ego nominatus abbas una cum meis successoribus predictam rem ut supra
                        legitur vobis vestrisque filiis ab omni persona ominum defensare, auctoriare
                        firmiterque tenere promitto. Si omnia supradicta non opservavero cum meis
                        successoribus et contra ec agere presumpserimus, tunc me meosque
                        successoresdaturos et composituros esse promitto vobis vestrisque filiis,
                        nomine pene, <rs key="#Penalty">auri unciam unam</rs>, et pena soluta maneat
                        firma omnia supradicta. Ego <persName key="#Tabellio"><name ref="Hughicio"
                                >Ugizo</name></persName> preclare urbis <placeName ref="#places/549"
                            >Ravenne</placeName>
                        <rs key="#Tabellio">tabellio</rs> ex nobili Porcinaclorum genere et
                        Pomposiani monasterii notarius iussu domini abbatis scripsi ec et complevi.
                        Nomina quidem testium adstancium et omnia audientium, idest: Iulianus et
                        Dominicus Gusca et Marsilius.</ab>
                </div>
